# Game Launch Flow Walkthrough

## Complete sequence when launching a Steam game from Library

### Phase 1: UI → Intent (UnifiedActivity.kt)

1. User taps **PLAY** on a Steam game → calls [launchSteamGame(context, containerManager, app)](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/UnifiedActivity.kt#950-1032)
2. [launchSteamGame](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/UnifiedActivity.kt#950-1032) does:
   - Gets `gameInstallPath` via `SteamService.getAppDirPath(app.id)` 
   - Checks if directory exists
   - Searches for existing `.desktop` shortcut matching `app_id`
   - **If shortcut exists**: Mounts A: drive on its container, starts [XServerDisplayActivity](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/XServerDisplayActivity.java#138-2180) with `container_id` + `shortcut_path`
   - **If no shortcut**: Gets or creates a container, mounts A: drive, creates a `.desktop` file, starts [XServerDisplayActivity](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/XServerDisplayActivity.java#138-2180)

### Phase 2: Activity Init (XServerDisplayActivity.java)

3. [onCreate()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/ContainersFragment.java#63-69) receives intent with `container_id` and `shortcut_path`
4. Loads `container` from `containerManager.getContainerById(containerId)`
5. Creates `shortcut = new Shortcut(container, new File(shortcutPath))`
6. The [Shortcut](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/container/Shortcut.java#21-317) constructor parses the `.desktop` file:
   - Extracts [Exec](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/container/Container.java#103-106) field → sets `shortcut.path` (via `StringUtils.unescape`)
   - Extracts `[Extra Data]` section → populates `extraData` JSONObject
   
7. **Container override**: If shortcut has `container_id` extra, switches to that container
8. **A: drive re-mount**: For Steam games, gets `gameInstallPath` via `SteamBridge.getAppDirPath()` and calls [mountADriveOnContainer(container, path)](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/XServerDisplayActivity.java#1899-1915) — this updates the container's [drives](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/Reference/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/container/Container.java#654-657) field and calls `container.saveData()`

### Phase 3: Wine version + Settings Override

9. `wineVersion = container.getWineVersion()` — base version
10. **NEW**: If shortcut has `wineVersion` extra, overrides `wineVersion` with that value
11. `wineInfo = WineInfo.fromIdentifier(this, contentsManager, wineVersion)` — determines Wine binary path and architecture ([x86_64](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/Reference/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/xenvironment/components/GuestProgramLauncherComponent.java#347-373) vs `arm64ec`)
12. Per-game settings overrides from shortcut extras:
    - `graphicsDriver`, `audioDriver`, `emulator`, `dxwrapper`, `screenSize`, etc.

### Phase 4: Boot Sequence

13. `boot()` → `setupWinePrefix()` → `onBoot()` → [setupXEnvironment()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/XServerDisplayActivity.java#1103-1237)
14. Inside boot:
    - Installs Wine components
    - Extracts Steam client if `container.isLaunchRealSteam()` is true
    - `WineUtils.createDosdevicesSymlinks(container)` — creates Wine drive symlinks including [a:](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/gradlew) → game directory
    - [setupXEnvironment()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/XServerDisplayActivity.java#1103-1237) is called

### Phase 5: Command Construction (setupXEnvironment)

15. Creates [GuestProgramLauncherComponent](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/Reference/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/xenvironment/components/GuestProgramLauncherComponent.java#28-440) with container and shortcut
16. Calls [getWineStartCommand()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/Reference/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/ui/screen/xserver/XServerScreen.kt#2285-2771) to build the Wine command args

#### [getWineStartCommand()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/Reference/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/ui/screen/xserver/XServerScreen.kt#2285-2771) for Steam games:
- Gets `game_source=STEAM` from shortcut extra
- Writes `ColdClientLoader.ini` via `SteamUtils.writeColdClientIni(appId, container)`
- Checks `shortcut.path`:
  - **If real Windows path** (not `steamclient_loader`, contains `\`): Uses `/dir` format
  - **If default/steamclient_loader**: Calls `SteamBridge.getAppDirPath(appId)` to find game dir, searches for `.exe` via [findGameExe()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/XServerDisplayActivity.java#2130-2147), builds `/dir A:\subdir "game.exe"` format
  - **If no exe found**: Falls back to `"wfm.exe"` (file manager)

17. Final command: `winhandler.exe /dir A:\subdir "game.exe"`
18. Full guest executable: `wine explorer /desktop=shell,800x600 winhandler.exe /dir A:\subdir "game.exe"`

### Phase 6: Process Execution (GuestProgramLauncherComponent)

19. [start()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/Reference/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/xenvironment/components/GuestProgramLauncherComponent.java#67-77) method constructs the native command:
    - **ARM64EC**: `<winePath>/bin/wine explorer /desktop=shell,800x600 winhandler.exe /dir A:\subdir "game.exe"`
    - **x86_64**: `<binDir>/box64 wine explorer /desktop=shell,800x600 winhandler.exe /dir A:\subdir "game.exe"`
20. `ProcessHelper.exec(command, envVars, rootDir, callback)` runs it

### Phase 7: Inside Wine

21. `wine explorer /desktop=shell,...` creates the virtual desktop
22. `winhandler.exe` receives the `/dir A:\subdir "game.exe"` and:
    - Sets working directory to `A:\subdir` 
    - Launches `game.exe`

## Steam DRM Integration

### ColdClientLoader (Goldberg Emu)
- Located at `C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\ColdClientLoader.ini`
- Written by `SteamUtils.writeColdClientIni()` with:
  - `AppId=<steamAppId>`
  - `Exe=steamapps\common\<gameName>\<executablePath>`
  - `SteamClientDll=steamclient.dll` / `SteamClient64Dll=steamclient64.dll`

### Steam Client Extraction
- `SteamClientManager.extractSteam()` extracts `steam.tzst` to `imagefs/opt/`
- Contains Goldberg Steam emulator files
- Triggered when `container.isLaunchRealSteam()` is true

### Steamless DRM Removal
- `SteamClientManager.runSteamless()` can strip DRM from executables
- Uses `z:\Steamless\Steamless.CLI.exe` inside Wine
- Backs up original, replaces with unpacked version

